Introduction¶

I have joined Udicity Scholarship. I have to do some work to apply what I have learnt in the content of course as a tangible application to use Python programming code,statistics, visualizations that will help in illustrating relations between attributes & answering to questions Using descriptive statistics, So I decide to investigate No show appointment dataset to translate all effort in my previous study to valuable work.

Findings

  1. The patient_id data type is float.
  2. There are 13 independent variables & one dependent (no_show) in the dataframe.
  3. There is not missing values (NaNs) in the dataframe.
  4. I should add new column contains difference between actual visit & scheduled visit after changing date to time
  5. The scheduled_day and appointment_day columns type should be changed to datetime.
  6. The appointment_day has specific hour (it equals to 00:00:00) this will make analysis will be complicated.
  7. I should ask a question about distribution of no-show &show with all day of week make a new column called appointment_dow

Conclusion¶

# I investigate No-show-Appointment dataset for Brazil healthcare system. There were some false values in the attributes of the dataset, So I remove wrong data, adding new features from the columns to help in analysis phase. I have also investigated relations between columns using visualizations. This analysis help me to understand more about attributes. I have noticed that: 1-From the figure Jardim camburi & Maria ortiz are recieving the most number of visits. 2-Visit appointments started on 2016-04-29 and ended on 2016-06-08. 3-Scheduling visits started on 2015-11-10 and ended on 2016-06-08. 4-Sonday has no visits & saturday is the least day of visits Tuesday is the most. 5-40% of patients only have visits in the same day & 60% have to wait which is a bad indicator. 6-The mean of ages is 37 years old & there were more than 110 (I consider them outliers & dropped). 7-The patients are 37 years on average. 25% of patients are below 18 and most of them are below 55. 8-The majority patient is non alcholic. 9-Handicap is categorized to 4 categories which cosidered as limitation because the handicaped are not classified according to thier disability as some times the disability do not have effects on patient to attend thier medical appointment (Deaf and dumb). 10-Most patients do not have hypertension. 11-Around 20% of appointments were missed. 12- In range (0:15) years old males is more than femals in show. 13- In range (15:60) years old the same in behaviour like females. 14- In range (15:60) years old men show more. 15-More than 100 both males & females no show 16-There are patients with more than one appoinpments. Limitations: 1- The four categories of handicap: Each category should be illustrated becuse there are disabled people can go to the clinical visits for example (Deaf and dumb) people because they can move and go to thier destinations without any problems. So I think the categories should be illustrated to predict & make a correct vision. 2-Adding distance between patient house & medical centre can help in prediction of No-show column result. it is a missing data & should be included. `
